body.description: Product Description Finally, a pacifier that soothes babies and parents too! The PhysioForma Soft Silicone Orthodontic Pacifier is a 100% silicone one-piece pacifier that isn't just for pacifying, but is also clinically developed for comfort, breathing and orthodontic benefits. An exclusive nipple design helps position baby’s tongue forward to maintain an open airway, which supports physiological breathing. Physiological breathing is especially important during sleep. It improves quality of sleep and reduces irritability - better for baby & you! The unique angle and lateral curve of the nipple evenly distribute tongue pressure across baby's palate. Tiny ridges and an inclined nipple shape guide proper tongue placement. Together, these important features support baby's growing palate and teeth.For baby’s comfort, the nipple is made from extra-soft silicone with a satin-textured finish to help keep the paci in baby’s mouth for uninterrupted soothing. Multiple ventilation holes promote air circulation and help reduce moisture buildup on baby’s soft, sensitive skin. Plus, there's an easy-to-grab handle for either baby or parent to hold. The PhysioForma exclusive nipple design was developed, tested, and approved in partnership with an advisory panel of leading neonatologists, pediatricians, and orthodontists. The one-piece Soft Silicone pacifiers also adhere to the guidelines of the American Academy of Pediatrics and are accepted by 9 out of 10 babies. Available in three sizes: 0-6m, 6-16m, and 16-24m. Reusable, sterilizing/carry case included. Brand Story By Chicco

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: A Perfect Fit for baby's comfort Soft, flexible, high quality silicone pacifier is comfortable & breathable. A contoured shield with 4 ventilation holes for air circulation fits baby's little face & helps reduce moisture buildup. Plus, an extra-soft nipple helps baby stay latched - for more comfort & less slip! Exclusive Nipple Design for baby's breathing Clinical studies show PhysioForma pacifiers actively support baby's breathing. Our exclusive nipple (developed, tested & approved in partnership with an advisory panel of neonatologists, pediatricians & orthodontists) helps position baby's tongue forward to maintain an open airway. Orthodontic Design for baby’s oral development Unique angle and lateral curve of the nipple evenly distribute tongue pressure across baby's palate. Tiny ridges and an inclined nipple shape guide proper tongue placement. Together, these important features support baby's growing palate and teeth! One-piece Construction for safety and hygiene Made from 100% food-grade silicone means there are no parts that can break apart & there is nowhere for germs to hide. One-piece pacifier adheres to the guidelines of the American Academy of Pediatrics. Another benefit of this design - an easy to grab handle for baby or parent to hold! Included Sterilizing Case for cleanliness In addition to being handy storage for baby's pacis, you can also use the included case to eliminate germs quickly and easily with the power of steam. Our sterilizing case lets you sanitize pacifiers in the microwave in just 3 minutes! Loved by Babies and Parents don't just take our word for it Parents voted and they endorse PhysioForma! Our one-piece, Soft Silicone Orthodontic Pacifiers received the 2020 National Parenting Product Award, the 2020 Mom's Choice Gold Award and the prestigious Parent Tested, Parent Approved Seal of Approval for the second year in a row.

Accessorize Your PhysioForma Choose Your Favorite Buddy Soft loveys make the perfect snuggle buddies and keep baby's paci close by. Attach pacifier to hand, tail or store in the roomy belly pocket. These cuddly friends are available in 4 friends: Bunny, Elephant, Fox, and Bear. Perfect for the paci stage and beyond. Long lasting. Machine washable. Fashionable Pacifier Clips Fashionable clips keep baby's pacis clean and within reach. Universal clips attach any style pacifier to baby's clothing, diaper bags, purses & more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My daughter loves these pacifiers. She was very picky and would only take one pacifier, after a day of using these she adjusted well. They are soft and easy for her to hold onto, she doesn’t spit them out. She is teething and loves to use them for her comfort. They’re also easy to wash off

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Completely Satisfied With This Purchase
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. These pacifiers are wonderful. I absolutely love them. Who loves them even more? My (nearly) 6 months old son.It was immediate. It's a great size for his mouth, which made it easy for him to get comfortable. It's soft all over; He enjoys taking it out of his mouth and adjusting it, so that he can chew it from any angle.I don't have to worry about it wearing anytime soon. Not only did I order 2 packs of 2 pacifiers, but it also has a decent thickness to it. I personally purchased the clear ones, but I will be getting the blue and green soon for a bit of variety.As for the shape, my only wish is that it was a bit more rounded at the top, because I feel like when pacifiers are shaped valley in the middle, the peaks tend to push the nostrils up. Luckily, this one does have a little bit of space. It doesn't curve on to his mouth. If that makes sense?Another thing that I like is the loop at the back of the pacifier that allows you to hook on a clip. I had another brand that does silicone pacifiers, and there wasn't anything to attach the clip to. As you can see, I have the ali+oli linen pacifier clips, and it works out perfectly.Overall, I am completely satisfied with this purchase, and I would recommend it to every mom.

reviews.reviewText: Both of my kids like these pacifiers. I like that they made in Italy, are easy to clean and have a loop to attach a leash to so they don't fall on the floor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy but Sticky
reviews.reviewText: My 2 year old son was chewing through all his pacifiers so we tried these and they are very sturdy. After about two weeks of using them (just at night) he has yet to do any damage. However, stuff sticks to them like crazy (fuzz from his stuffed animals, dust when they fall out of the crib, moms hair, etc.) so you have to clean them off a lot.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good but not good
reviews.reviewText: I started with the 0-2 months pacifier, my son is almost 4 months old so I decided to order the blue pacifier which is made for 6-16 months. I didn’t think it would be a problem considering he would grow into it, but unfortunately the blue pacifier is too big for his mouth and when he’s not actively sucking him, the pacifier will make him gag. So I ordered the 2-6 months and a bit confused/disappointed. The 2-6 months pacifier appears to be the same size as the 0-2 months one but it’s not. It’s actually smaller and the nipple is shorter. I tried my best to show that in the pictures. Not happy with this dilemma because I don’t think it’s a good to give my son a smaller nipple even if it’s it not that much smaller. Anyway, these will just be backups until he grows into the blue ones! Also I don’t like the texture of the blue ones, they are much stickier and basically a lint roller! Every little fiber of lint sticks to it and does not fall off, it’s needs to be washed! Ugh!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best in my opinion
reviews.reviewText: Both of my babies loved this pacifier. We have tried plenty of different ones and this is the one they stuck with. They both had all three colors. I wish they had more colors to offer though and when my babies got to around one they started to drool too much even with the right size pacifier. I would purchase again
